AS winter approaches, so the possibility of fires increases. Ekurhuleni emergency services spokesman William Ntladi warned SunLanders to be vigilant during the chilly season. He said: “With the right preparation, adults and children can prevent injuries and deaths.” Ntladi shared the following tips: Those who use gas heaters must remember the following: Ntladi also advised SunLanders to install smoke and carbon monoxide detecters in their homes. He said: “Carbon monoxide and hydrogen cyanide are some of the gases emitted by burning coals. “They are known as killer gases because they are not easy to detect.”